# Styling Guidelines

- Use CSS Modules for component-specific styles
- Global styles should only be defined in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
- Follow BEM naming convention for class names
- Use CSS variables for theme values (colors, spacing, etc.)
- Prefer relative units (rem, em) over fixed units (px)
- Use flexbox and grid for layouts
- Maintain mobile-first responsive design
- Keep specificity low by avoiding deep nesting
- Use PostCSS features as configured in [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs)